bits

Class BooleanLiteral

  • java.lang.Object
    • bits.BooleanLiteral
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBooleanLiteral, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>

    public class BooleanLiteral
extends java.lang.Object
implements IBooleanLiteral
    A class which represents a Boolean literal. BooleanLiteral is essentially a BooleanVariable together with a boolean indicating whether the BooleanVariable is barred (negated) or not. NOTE: Alternative implementations of BooleanLiteral must not only implement IBooleanLiteral, but must also ensure that any two instances of BooleanLiteral are equal if and only if they agree on the value of barred, and contain equal instances of BooleanVariable.
    Version:
    1.0, 04/09/07
    Author:
    Kerry Michael Soileau

      • getBooleanLiteral

        public static IBooleanLiteral getBooleanLiteral(IBooleanVariable bv,
                                                boolean barred)
                                         throws BooleanLiteralException
        Rather than providing a public constructor for the BooleanLiteral class, a static factory method is instead provided. This is to avoid duplication of a already-existing IBooleanLiteral. The HashSet instances is searched to determine whether an IBooleanLiteral with the desired internal IBooleanVariable and barred-ness already exists; if it does, the instance is returned. If not, the private constructor is used to create the desired IBooleanLiteral, which is then added to the HashSet instances and is returned.
        Throws:
        BooleanLiteralException

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        If o is null, this method returns false. If o is not of type IBooleanLiteral, this method returns false. If the Object passed has a different internal IBooleanVariable, this method returns false. If the "barred-ness" of this and o is different, this method returns false. Otherwise, this method returns true.
